data.content:
## What breaks: Cosmos DB sync I/O is **fully removed** in EF Core 11

In .NET 10, the Cosmos provider's sync-over-async opt-in let you keep `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, and `SaveChanges()`. In EF Core 11, **that opt-in no longer exists** — all synchronous I/O APIs **always throw**, regardless of configuration.

### Every method in your repository breaks:

| Sync (breaks) | Async replacement |
|---|---|
| `ToList()` | `await ToListAsync()` |
| `First(...)` | `await FirstAsync(...)` |
| `Count()` | `await CountAsync()` |
| `SaveChanges()` | `await SaveChangesAsync()` |

### Fixed code:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**All callers** of these methods must also be updated to `await` the results. This will ripple up through your call chain (controllers, services, etc.).

Tracking issue: https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059
